<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-310-150  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 310 150.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  March 19 1990 v36 n1801 p38(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>HP offers Boundary Scan language. (Boundary Scan DescriptionLanguage)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dunn, Peter.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>HP, in an effort to establish a de facto standard, is developingthe Boundary Scan Description Language (BSDL), a descriptionlanguage for the design of integrated circuits (ICs).andP;  Theapplication is designed to offer an easily understood descriptionof the boundary scan implementation for an individual IC.andP;  Testand design vendors, without having to develop their ownmethodology, could use the descriptions in simulators, testprogram generators and other software tools.andP;  The ICs willprobably include BSDL code that explains the pinout and internalscan cell structure as part of the package.andP;  Users could importthe data into test generation packages and simulators that supportthe standard.andP;  Other companies are supporting HP's efforts and areproviding feedback on additional solutions.andP;  HP hopes to publishthe standard at the International Test Conference during the fallof 1990.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hewlett-Packard Co. (research).andO;Ticker:    HWP.andO;Topic:     Computer industryTestingStandardsIntegrated circuits.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>